Key Match Events: Rookie starter Sam Aldeghri allowed four earned runs, five walks, six hits, and zero strikeouts in two innings.
Astros’ starter Yusei Kikuchi threw an impressive seven innings of work, allowing only three earned runs while throwing six strikeouts.
Tyler Anderson started the game and threw a middle-of-the-pack outing, lasting five innings and allowing four earned runs.
Catcher Logan O’Hoppe had a great showing with two hits, one RBI and scoring a run.
Three-time Cy Young winner Justin Verlander gave up two earned runs, four hits and walked a couple in five innings.
Astros reliever Ryan Pressly shut down the chance of any comeback with a 1.2 inning save.
Caden Dana only managed to stay in the game for 3.1 innings, allowing four earned runs.
Taylor Ward started the offensive run with a solo homer in the final game of the series.
